      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your desire to avoid the hassle of a doctor's visit, but self-treatment can be risky, especially with high doses of vitamins. The recommended safe upper limit for vitamin D is 4,000 IU for adults, and exceeding this can lead to toxicity. Short-term high doses can cause side effects like nausea, vomiting, weakness, and serious complications like kidney damage. It's always best to consult a healthcare professional to determine the safest and most effective way to address your concerns.",
      "source": "target",
